Package: spida
Type: Package
Title: Collection of miscellaneous functions for mixed models etc. prepared for SPIDA 2009+ (development version)
Version: 0.1.4.9999
Date: 2015-11-29
Author: Georges Monette
Maintainer: Georges Monette <georges@yorku.ca>
Description: Collection of utility functions for mixed models including
   wald:  Wald test with functions to generate hypothesis matrices
   gsp:   general spline with any degree and smoothness with additional
          function 'sc' to contruct hypotheses,
   smsp:  tool for smoothing splines with lme and nlme based on lmeSplines
   capply: create contextual variables. Also: cvar, dvar, up, xapply
   Misc:  vif.lme, xqplot, tab, panel.subgroups (additional level of subgroups in xyplot), multresp
Depends: lattice, foreign
Suggests: Hmisc, magrittr, knitr, car
License: GPL (>= 2)
URL: http://georges.blog.yorku.ca
LazyLoad: yes
LazyData: yes
VignetteBuilder: knitr
